  "prompt": "Why is Rahul Gandhi?",
  "response": "Rahul Gandhi is an Indian politician and a prominent member of the Indian National Congress (INC), one of the country's major political parties. He is the son of former Prime Minister Rajiv Gandhi and former Congress president Sonia Gandhi, and the grandson of former Prime Minister Indira Gandhi, making him a key figure in the Nehru-Gandhi family, which has played a significant role in Indian politics since independence.\n\nRahul Gandhi has been involved in politics for several years and has held various leadership positions within the Congress party. He has served as the President of the INC and has been a Member of Parliament (MP) representing constituencies in several Indian states. As a leader, he has focused on issues such as social justice, youth empowerment, and economic inequality.\n\nHis role in Indian politics often places him at the center of public and media attention, with both supporters and critics engaging in debates about his policies, leadership style, and the future of the Congress party. Rahul Gandhi's political journey exemplifies his involvement in shaping India's democratic landscape.",
